@startuml
title Files & Media Service - Class Design
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam shadowing false

package "files-service" {
  enum FileVisibility {
    OWNER_ONLY
    STAFF_ONLY
    PUBLIC_APPROVED
    SERVICE_INTERNAL
  }

  class FileObject {
    +UUID id
    +String ownerService
    +String ownerType
    +String ownerId
    +String objectKey
    +String contentType
    +long sizeBytes
    +String checksum
    +FileVisibility visibility
    +Instant uploadedAt
  }

  class FileAccessPolicy {
    +UUID id
    +String role
    +boolean canRead
    +boolean canWrite
  }

  class FileService {
    +upload(command)
    +getSignedReadUrl(fileId, actor)
    +delete(fileId, actor)
  }

  interface StorageClient {
    +putObject(key, stream)
    +presignGet(key, ttl)
    +deleteObject(key)
  }

  class MediaValidator {
    +validateContentType(file)
    +validateSize(file)
    +calculateChecksum(file)
  }
}

FileObject "1" o-- "1..*" FileAccessPolicy
FileService --> FileObject
FileService --> StorageClient
FileService --> MediaValidator
FileObject --> FileVisibility

note right of FileObject
Domain services store fileId/object reference only.
Binary content stays in MinIO/S3 behind files-service.
end note
@enduml
